Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil on high heat. Chop the @potatoes{450}(peeled and into 2cm chunks). Add them to the water with a @salt{0.25%tsp}. Bring back to the boil. Once boiling reduce the heat slightly and cook until the potatoes are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. When cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Preheat your #oven{} to 200 °C.

Meanwhile, put the @Dried Italian Herbs{1} (Italian seasoning), @panko breadcrumbs{12.5%g} and @water{1%tbsp} per person into a large #mixing bowl{}. Mix together, then add the @British Pork Mince{120%g} and @British Beef Mince{120%g}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Use your hands to mix the seasonings into the meat then shape into small balls (5 per person).

> TIP: Make sure you roll them well in the palms of your hands to prevent them falling apart when cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the meatballs and cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}, turning occasionally.

> TIP: Do this in batches if necessary, you want the meatballs to brown not stew!

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1/2}. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}. When the meatballs are browned, transfer to a #plate{} then drain any remaining fat out of the pan. Add the onion and @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{120%g} to the pan. Cook until the onion is soft, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the meatballs back into the pan.

Add the @Water for the Sauce{125%ml} and the @Chicken Stock Powder{1} to the pan. Stir then return the meatballs and lower the heat. Cover the pan with a #lid{} or #foil{} and simmer until the meatballs are cooked through, ~{7-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve any large @Broccoli Florets{200} and pop them on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Roast in the oven until browned and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Mash the potatoes in the pan then stir in the grated cheddar. Season to taste with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Keep warm with the lid on while you finish off.

> TIP: Add a splash of milk and a knob of butter if you have it.

When the meatballs are cooked through, remove the lid and stir in the @Redcurrant Jelly{25%g}. Increase the heat and bubble the sauce until it is glossy and has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Share the mash between your plates and serve the broccoli florets alongside. Pop the meatballs on top of the mash and finish with a generous helping of gravy. Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've chosen to receive extra bacon, just follow the recipe as instructed!